</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="621" pageNumber="622" type="note">
<paragraph pageId="621" pageNumber="622">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="621" pageNumber="622">
The name 
<taxonomicName class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Chlaenius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="621" pageNumber="622" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dimidiatus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="621" pageNumber="622">Chlaenius dimidiatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Motschulsky, 1858 is often listed as a junior synonym of this species (e.g., Csiki 1931: 971; Bell 1960: 115). However, Motschulsky never provided a description of the taxon and the name is a 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="621" pageNumber="622">nomen nudum</emphasis>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
